From c994abf8989776aa9ad4e168d3d4f59d84e00b76 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: radhevrishi <radhev.232@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 13:39:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 10/17] feat(india): institutional one-liner verdict + concall
 noise filter + trend gap fix
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User feedback after Intellect Design Arena test:
- Wanted a top-line summary 'so I know already what to do with this
  company' — verdict + headline + watch points at a glance
- Three of four top quotes were procedural (dividend record dates,
  officer retirement notice) — not concall content
- Quarterly Trend (8Q) had three blank rows because NSE returned
  only 5 quarters and Screener was overridden
- Guidance card showed 'no language matched' even though the deck
  described a Stage 4 ₹1,500 Cr multi-year product target

A. ONE-LINER INSTITUTIONAL VERDICT
   New buildTopLineVerdict() helper synthesises four pieces from
   the snapshot data into a single actionable line:
    - VERDICT pill: BUY / ACCUMULATE / HOLD / NEUTRAL / AVOID / SELL,
      derived from FundamentalScore × direction
    - Headline sentence: directional (e.g. 'QoQ rebound after weak
      YoY trend', 'Strong YoY growth across revenue and profit',
      'Revenue softening but profit holding up — margin tailwind')
    - Rationale clause incorporating the most material risk flag
      (cash conversion weak, working capital stretched, promoter
      dilution, margin pressure)
    - Watch points: top 3 critical sector KPIs

   Rendered as a colored-border box right under the company name,
   above the Fundamentals-mode banner. Verdict pill colored by
   verdict (green BUY → red SELL). Reads in two glances.

B. PROCEDURAL DISCLOSURE FILTER
   New isProceduralDisclosure() — rejects sentences containing:
   record date, book closure, AGM/EGM/postal ballot, dividend
   payment dates, officer retirement/superannuation/cessation,
   committee changes, Regulation 30/31/76 references, formal date
   strings ('Friday, July 24, 2026'). Applied as a hard -100 score
   in scoreSentence + filtered from sentence array before topic
   matching. Top quotes now skip dividend-calendar and
   board-change announcements.

C. EMPTY TREND-ROW FIX
   qtrendBase now filters by quarters.sales !== null before slicing
   the last 8. Prevents Jun/Sep/Dec 2024 (or any pre-data periods)
   from rendering as '—'-filled rows. Trend table only shows real
   quarters.

D. STAGE-GATE / MULTI-YEAR TARGET GUIDANCE
   inferGuidance now detects:
    - 'Stage [N]' / 'Phase [N]' / 'Year [N]' followed by a ₹X Cr or
      USD X mn target (Intellect's Stage 4 ₹1,500 Cr fired)
    - 'X-year cycle/plan/roadmap/target/horizon' or 'aspires to /
      aspirational target / target of ₹X'
   Both classify as 'introduced' direction (concrete forward plan
   without explicit raise/lower keyword). Guidance card now flips
   to '● available' for product roadmap-driven decks.

